					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-474150#post-1473136</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-474150/scp-1618#post-1473136</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jun 2012 01:07:10 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>VAElynx</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>914331</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Oh Bastet. (I seen this silly pop up in the SA thread, so I actually bother to address it)</p> <p>Why Duchamp's Fountain - because it looks like an urinal?</p> <p>Seriously - the focus of this comes from the quote cited at the bottom, which calls for a golden toilet of some sort, and given various considerations (executives inside the building being primary target, urinals being outside rather than closed in cabins making the leaflet message somewhat more noticeable,me simply liking the picture of the gilded urinal, and it being the first thing I thought of when off to make the SCP) I chose an urinal. However, the whole object wouldn't change a single bit if it was an actual toilet.</p> <p>Furthermore, the point of the fountain was a piece of no-effort failart that the guy tried to enter in a competition to take the piss off the other entries. this has again nothing to do with that.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
